1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
An event horizon isn't a wall; it's a boundary beyond which nothing escapes.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:09,600
Imagine a point in space where escape speed equals light speed.

3
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:10,400
That's it.

4
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:14,000
Once you cross this point, no signal can escape.

5
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,200
Not even light.

6
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:20,000
This boundary marks the limits of our observable universe around black holes.

7
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:24,800
Understanding event horizons helps us grasp the mysteries of gravity and spacetime.

8
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,400
Curious about black holes?

9
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,400
Follow for more mind-bending science!
